              <span id="reviewTextContainer2485310" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16249295283894082691">This book, though heavy in military jargon and very long, was absolutely one of the most stunning books I have ever read. It was gripping, and completely chilling. It is the deeply personal story of Romeo Daillaire, the head of the UN Peacekeeping mission for Rwanda during the genocide/war and how he witnessed, literally, the abandonment of humanity by humanity.<br/><br/>It is worth your time to read this book. I plan to read it again soon.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


