    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2957426051" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2957426051" />
    <a title="UnusualChild{beppy}" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9969735-unusualchild-beppy"><img alt="UnusualChild{beppy}" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1501695960p2/9969735.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2957426051?book_show_action=true">Oct 31, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="UnusualChild{beppy}" class="user" itemprop="url" name="UnusualChild{beppy}" href="/user/show/9969735-unusualchild-beppy">UnusualChild{beppy}</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=library">library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=fight-the-good-fight">fight-the-good-fight</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=4-5-stars">4-5-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=i-say">i-say</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=about-me-them">about-me-them</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2957426051" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer975225195881226035">4.5 stars<br/><br/>Romeo Dallaire was in charge of the Peacekeeping initiative in Rwanda in 1993. There was supposed to be an accord between two warring tribes, and the Peacekeepers were there to make sure everything was followed, and then pull out. Dallaire was working with limited resources and forces, as the UN and its&apos; nations were more focused on Somalia and Croata/Bosnia/eastern Europe at the time. In spite of his team&apos;s best efforts at brokering and enforcing peace, Dallaire was on hand for the gen</span>
  <span id="freeText975225195881226035" style="display:none">4.5 stars<br /><br />Romeo Dallaire was in charge of the Peacekeeping initiative in Rwanda in 1993. There was supposed to be an accord between two warring tribes, and the Peacekeepers were there to make sure everything was followed, and then pull out. Dallaire was working with limited resources and forces, as the UN and its' nations were more focused on Somalia and Croata/Bosnia/eastern Europe at the time. In spite of his team's best efforts at brokering and enforcing peace, Dallaire was on hand for the genocide of over 800,000 people in a period of 3 months.<br /><br />This was...I don't know. Horrifying. Edifying. Shocking. Personal. Thought provoking.<br /><br />Why do humans do this to each other? What makes one subset think that they are better than one another? I mean, animals fight for dominance, and if they don't kill each other, the loser leaves the territory. But animals don't kill every other living thing in order to make a point. It's only humans that do so, so you can't say that it's nature.<br />While I was reading this, I never once got the feeling that Dallaire was making excuses for what happened between April and June 1993. He was just stating what happened while he was in Rwanda, and accepted responsibility, as leaders do, for the soldiers who died under his watch. He felt as though he may not have been able to give the opposing sides his full attention to ascertain whether or not their intentions were good, since he often ended up translating instead of being involved in the conversation. He also felt as though not enough emphasis was being placed on lives being a resource, given the fact that very few countries pledged troops or equipment to the mission. And while he was frustrated with that, even 10 years later, his intent was to tell the truth about what happened.</span>
  <a data-text-id="975225195881226035" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


